cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper is about a framework for RGBT tracking, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel metric learning framework, which involves designing a structured loss and exploiting the structured information of all samples in each modality. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (learning), cs.MM (multimodal learning), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves tracking objects, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (robotics) sub-category.
